absence of biofilm formation

value.value: A biofilm formation phenotype where a microbe is incapable of forming a biofilm.

label.value: decreased vegetative cell diameter

value.value: An altered cell size phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle where the diameter of a microbial cell with a circular cross-section is decreased relative to a designated control.

label.value: cell size variability

definition.value: A cell population phenotype that describes the extent of cell size variability within a growing microbial cell population.

increased anaerobic population growth

value.value: An altered anaerobic population growth phenotype where growth of a microbial population in the absence of O2 is increased relative to a designated control.

definition.value: Altered population growth may result from changes in population growth rate or population growth yield. Consider using a more specific term if either of these parameters was determined in the experiments.

label.value: decreased anaerobic population growth

value.value: An altered anaerobic population growth phenotype where growth of a microbial population in the absence of O2 is decreased relative to a designated control.

definition.value: Altered population growth may result from changes in population growth rate or population growth yield. Consider using a more specific term if either of these parameters was determined in the experiments.

label.value: commonly used descriptors

value.value: Microbial taxa are commonly described in terms of phenotypic characteristics that are shared by all or almost all members of a particular taxonomic group.

label.value: decreased microaerophilic population growth

value.value: A population growth phenotype where growth of a microbial population in a microaerophilic environment is decreased relative to a designated control.

definition.value: Altered population growth may result from changes in population growth rate or population growth yield. Consider using a more specific term if either of these parameters was determined in the experiments.

label.value: increased microaerophilic population growth

value.value: An altered microaerophilic population growth phenotype where growth of a microbial population in a microaerophilic environment is increased relative to a designated control.

definition.value: Altered population growth may result from changes in population growth rate or population growth yield. Consider using a more specific term if either of these parameters was determined in the experiments.

label.value: altered population phenotype

value.value: A microbial population phenotype where the phenotype of a microbial population is altered in some way relative to a designated control.

label.value: resistance to nutrient limitation stress phenotype

value.value: A resistance to stress phenotype related to the resistance or sensitivity of a microbial population to limitation for an essential nutrient.

label.value: presence of resistance to nutrient limitation

value.value: A resistance to stress phenotype where a microbial population is resistant to limitation for an essential nutrient.

label.value: absence of resistance to nutrient limitation

value.value: A resistance to stress phenotype where a microbial population isn't resistant to limitation for an essential nutrient.

label.value: altered resistance to nutrient limitation

value.value: A resistance to stress phenotype where the resistance of a microbial population to nutrient limitation is altered relative to a designated control.

increased ploidy in a vegetative microbial cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sets of chromosomes in a microbial cell, i.e. ploidy, increases relative to the designated control.

label.value: increased spontaneous diploidization in a vegetative microbial cell

value.value: An altered cell phenotype observed in the vegetative phase of the life cycle in which haploid microbial cells spontaneously form cells with diploid DNA content at a higher frequency than the designated control.

value.value: A population growth phenotype where a microbial population isn't  able to grow and reproduce at acidic pH (pH< 7).

label.value: altered population growth at high temperature

value.value: A population growth phenotype where the rate and/or extent of growth of a microbial population at a temperature that is towards the upper end of the organism's temperature growth range is altered relative to a designated control.
